
[1]dressing

   DRESSING, ppr. Adjusting to a line; putting in order; preparing;
   clothing; embellishing; cultivating.

   DRESSING, n.

   1. Raiment; attire.

   2. That which is used as an application to a wound or sore.

   3. That which is used in preparing land for a drop; manure spread over
   land. When it remains on the surface, it is called a top-dressing.

   4. In popular language, correction; a flogging, or beating.
